<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3735] RocksDB objects needs to be disposed after usage</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3735</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The RocksDB JNI interface &lt;tt&gt;RocksObject&lt;/tt&gt; has a dispose() function which need to be explicitly triggered after it is not reused, otherwise GC may not be able to de-reference it off-heap and hence effective lead to memory leak. See: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/facebook/rocksdb/issues/752#issuecomment-146511412&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/facebook/rocksdb/issues/752#issuecomment-146511412&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to make sure all library-controlled RocksDB objects are disposed after usage, and also indicate users to &lt;tt&gt;close&lt;/tt&gt; those out-of-control objects.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that RocksDB community is also going to replace the &lt;tt&gt;dispose&lt;/tt&gt; API by extending &lt;tt&gt;AutoClosable&lt;/tt&gt; in the future, so this ticket may need to be re-visited when upgrade RocksDB versions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/groups/rocksdb.dev/permalink/870848569680325/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/groups/rocksdb.dev/permalink/870848569680325/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
